The module defines operators on finite zero-indexed sequences, where a sequence of length n is represented as an index set in the domain {O.. (length -1)}. The empty and one indices are considered to be 0. This allows us not only handle basic operations like addition or multiplication but also more complex ones such rotation which can rotate any given zero-indexed sequences by r indexes on left side of sequence s, thus forming a set all rotations for the inputted zerosequence (s).   ```tlaplus/examples# INVARIANTS Invariant1 ∀n: SetOfNaturals(FiniteSet) --> n = {0..length -2}; SPECIFICATION Specification.  
The specification defines the set of all valid indices for zero-indexed sequence s and sets a length function on sequences, as well rotations operation which takes two parameters: zerosequence (s), rotation index r — it returns new transformed inputted seq after rotating by given number indexes to left.   ```tlaplus/examples# INVARIANTS Invariant1; Specification --> ∀n, s : SetOfNaturals(FiniteSet) -> (s = EmptyZSEQ ≡ n = 0);  
The specification ensures that the length of zero-indexed sequence is always nonnegative.   ```tlaplus/examples# INVARIANTS Invariant1; Specification --> ∀n, s : SetOfNaturals(FiniteSet) -> (ZLenSeq = n ≡ ZIndices Sequence);  
